Three people are to appear in court after police seized heroin, cannabis and diazepam in Dundee drugs raids. Police seize heroin and cannabis in Dundee drugs raids Three people are to appear in court after police seized heroin, cannabis and diazepam in Dundee drugs raids.
Officers executed warrants at addresses in the Douglas area of the city following an intelligence-led operation.
Drugs with a potential street value of more than &pound;2,500 were recovered, along with a four-figure sum of cash.
Men aged 32 and 42 and a 36-year-old woman were arrested and are expected to appear at Dundee Sheriff Court.
 